   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF THE MINOR PROPHETS MESSAGE TWENTY-ONE ON JONAH JEHOVAH S CARE AND SALVATION</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>TO THE MOST EVIL CITY OF THE GENTILES Scripture Reading: Jonah 1 4</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In this message we will consider the book of Jonah.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Among the books of the Minor Prophets, Jonah stands alone.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>I. THE INTRODUCTORY WORD</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Jonah 1:1-2 is the introductory word to this book.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>A. The Meaning of the Name Jonah</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Jonah in Hebrew means dove v. 1 . This signifies that God wanted Jonah to go out as a dove to preach the gospel of peace.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>B. The Time of Jonah s Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The time of Jonah s ministry was about 862 B.C., at the time of the prophet Elisha 896-838 B.C. .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>C. The Object of His Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The object of his ministry was the people of the great city of Nineveh, the capital of Assyria.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>D. The Place of His Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The place of his ministry also was Nineveh.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>E. The Subject of His Ministry</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The subject of Jonah s ministry was that Jehovah s salvation reached even to the Gentile city Nineveh.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>F. The Central Thought</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The central thought of the book of Jonah is that God cared for and saved even the most evil Gentiles in His pity on men and cattle.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>G. The Revelation concerning Christ</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In the book of Jonah, the revelation concerning Christ is in Jonah s being a type of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>In Jonah sTypifying Christ</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Preaching the Gospel of Peace to the Gentiles</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Christ is revealed in Jonah s typifying Christ preaching the gospel of peace to the Gentiles 3:2; Matt 12:41 .</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Jonah was a prophet who turned from Israel to the Gentiles.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>In this he was a type of Christ, who turned from Israel to the Gentiles Luke 4:25-27; Matt 21:43 .</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>In Jonah s Staying in the Great Fish</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Three Days and Three Nights</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Christ is revealed also in the type of Jonah s staying in the great fish three days and three nights Jonah 1:17 .</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>This typifies Christ s staying in the heart of the earth three days and three nights Matt 12:40 .</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Christ died and entered into the heart of the earth.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>He came forth from there in resurrection, and in resurrection He became the life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b for the preaching, the spreading, of the gospel to all the Gentile nations, as seen in the book of Acts.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>H. The Sections</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The book of Jonah has five sections: the introductory word 1:1-2 ; Jonah s fleeing from Jehovah s commission 1:2-17 ; Jonah s repenting ch.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>2 ; Jonah s preaching ch.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>3 ; and Jonah s prejudice ch.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>4 .</S>
   </TEXT>
